{
  "texts": [
    "Notice that this path does not need to correspond to a Stokes arrow.",
    "Figure 13.",
    "The monodromy data defining the Stokes local system with respect to a basepoint (in magenta) and the deformation data (in black) for the system after Fourier transform.",
    "Now, the parallel transport along the path we considered above corresponds to the matrix -1 0 0 1 S 2 -1 0 0 1 -1",
    "(go back to the basepoint via a partial formal monodromy, follow the loop associated with S 2 and go away from the basepoint again), and the number associated to its deformation datum corresponds to the (1, 2)-entry of this matrix, so we get the equation -a = -1, and hence S 2 = 1 1 0 1."
  ]
}